review_blob: 330 ml bottle.  Pours a dark brown with a big tan head.  Head reduces to a nice looking film on top that leaves some intricate lacing around the glass.   Aroma is alcohol, bread, strong plum and raisins, and some spices.  The alcohol is very noticeable in the taste, along with the many other flavors similar to the aroma.  Very complex and balanced.  Sweet with a light bitter finish.  Creamy and medium bodied with a good amount of carbonation.  Overall an excellent beer and one to be thoroughly enjoyed.

22. oz bomber.  Pours a cloudy, deep amber color with a smallish head.  Head leaves nice lacing around the inside of my tulip.  Aroma is very nice.  Orange peel, some grapefruit, lemon, a hint of apple, and sweet malts really jump out at you.  There is a definite aroma of alcohol as well.  Taste is sweet up front with a big hop bitterness on the back end.  More fruit and caramel in the taste.  Texture is good.  Medium body and slick/creamy.  Finish is really bitter, but really good.  Not the most complex barleywine, but a very good one.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Barleywine Style Ale

review_blob: 12. oz. bottle.  This is beer is beyond great.  Im not going to go into detail describing this beer because simply put, it is special.  If you like HUGE hops, balanced perfectly with a sweet malty backbone, you will like this brew.  It is the best Imperial IPA in the world.  Love this beer!

12 oz bottle.  Pours completely black with absolutely no head whatsoever.   This is such a wonderful beer.  A superb aroma of roasted coffee beans, chocolate, caramel, oats, and a little earth.  The taste is equally impressive with a HUGE roastiness.  Coffee and bittersweet chocolate come together perfectly.  A full bodied brew with minimal carbonation.  A semi creamy texture leads to a nice bitter finish.  Excellent all the way around.

12 oz. bottle.  This was a nice surprise.  Pours a pitch black color with a frothy brown head which quickly disappears to nothing.  Aroma of chocolate, coffee, roasted malts, a touch of caramel.  Very nice.  Flavor is roasty, coffee, and chocolate.  My only complaint would be too much carbonation, but I was pleasantly surprised by this offering from Mt. Carmel Brewing.  A really good stout.

12. bottle.  Pours a cloudy,  medium amber color with a minimal off white head.  Aroma is bready malt and some citrus and floral hops.  Pretty well balanced with a nice malt flavor up front and a decent lasting hop bitterness at the finish.  Medium body.  A decent IPA, but nothing special.

12 oz. bottle.  Pours an amber-brown color with a fluffy off white head.  Aroma of grass, sugar, dark fruit, citrus, caramel, toffee, bread, and spices.  Taste is plum, grass, and other floral notes, along with some grapefruit.  Pretty sweet up front but is followed nicely by a hop bitterness that carries it the rest of the way through.  The alcohol is well hidden and kind of sneaks up on you as you finish it.  Really good beer.
UPDATED: FEB 9, 2010

Draught @ Southpark Tavern, Dayton, OH.  Amazing beer.  Maple syrup, bourbon, chocolate, wood, raisin, vanilla all come together perfectly.  The mouthfeel is so creamy and smooth with the alchohol peaking through the array of flavors.  Pretty sweet beer, but overall just a great, great beer.

Draught @ Southpark Tavern, Dayton, OH.  Reddish orange pour with an off white head that lingers for a few minutes.  Nice lacing.  Aroma of grass, hay, and caramel malts, along with some floral hops.  The rye stands out, balanced nicely by the malts.  Thin to medium body with a dry bitter finish.  Nice beer.

Draught @ Southpark Tavern, Dayton, OH.  Wow.  Clear golden color with a nice white head.  A slight achohol aroma is accompanied by a HUGE piney, hop and malt ensemble.  Taste is more hops, but nicely balanced by the malts.  Big hop bitterness.  Texture is a little sticky with nice carbonation.  The smooth bitter finish is very nice.  This is an excellent, excellent beer.

12. oz bottle into snifter.  Pours a beautiful amber color with minimal, frothy white head that disappears rather quickly, leaving a nice ring of bubbles around the edge of the glass.  Aroma of massive hops.  Piney, earthy, a little citrus, and malts.  Taste is more hops.  Heavy, glorious, hoppy bitterness, but balanced nicely by the malty backbone.  Medium body with nice carbonation.  Finish is long lasting bitterness.  What a great IPA!  Thank God I still have 4 left.

Draught @ the Cincinnati location.  Golden color with a small white head.  A decent Belgian strong ale.  Flavors were dough, bread, banana, and some spices.  The 10.2% abv was well hidden.  Medium body and kind of oily.  A mildy sweet finish.  I would order this again.

Draught @ the Cincinnati location.  Pretty standard pale ale.  The deScription says, "for hopheads only".  Aroma of citrus and slight floral.  Taste was a little citrusy, piney, and dirty water.  Pretty light and thin on the palate with average carbonation.  Abrupt bitter finish.  Pretty forgetable.

12 oz. bottle.  Fantastic barleywine!  Pours a dark brown with a tan head that fades to a nice ring of bubbles around the edge of the glass.  Aroma of bread, nuts, some caramel, dough, a touch of alchohol.  Taste is soooo good.  More caremel, toffee, dough, a little dark fruit and a litle bit of floral notes.  Texture is creamy with nice carbonation followed by a small bitter finish.  Great beer to drink on a sub-freezing evening, as I am right now.

1 pint 6 oz. bottle.  This is a BIG beer!!  Lots of flavors.  Big malt presence on the front followed by a hoppy bitterness.  Great looking beer in my tulip.  Great feel in the mouth, thick and chewy.  The alchohol makes itself known too.

12 oz. bottle.  Pours a cloudy dark golden color with medium whitish head.  Head doesnt last long as it leaves a thin layer on top and bubbles around the edge of the glass.  Aroma of hops.  Lots of citrus hops and some sweet bready malts.  Taste is excellent.  Very well balanced IPA.  Citrusy and floral hops along with the sweet malts.  Finish is a very nice hoppy bitterness that hangs around a while.

Bottle.  Pours a really cloudy golden color with a big white head, naturally.  Aroma of spice, banana, clove, and dough.  Taste is very good.  More banana and spice with some bubblegum.  Light body with nice texture.  Very refreshing.  Excellent hefeweizen.

Draught at Southpark Tavern, Dayton, OH.   Deep amber color.  Aroma was massive citrus and floral hops.  Is this a barleywine or a IIPA?  Taste was more hops, but on the back end was balanced nicely by some sweet malts.  Finish was hoppy bitterness.  An overall subtle complexity, but an excellent beer that I really enjoyed.

12 oz. bottle.  Pours a cloudy gold with a frothy, white head.  Lots of floaties swirling around the glass (not a great pour).  Something was off with this beer.  The aroma was of floral and citrus hops.  Taste was hops and basement funk.  Finish was semi-bitter.

Excellent mahogany color, as the deScription states, with a small, quickly dissapating head.  Aroma of some dark fruit, but nothing really standing out.  Taste is sweet malts, fruit, a hint of raisins.  Finish is nice with some peaches lingering on the palate.  A quality beer.

12 oz bottle.  Pours a cloudy, golden color with a nice frothy white head.  Lots of tiny bubbles quickly quickly burst up from the bottom.  Highly carbonated.  Aroma is raspberries and not much else.  It drinks very light, with a tart raspberry flavor.  Thin texture and medium body.  Really fizzy in the mouth.  Finish is...there really isnt a finish.  It just kind of goes away quickly.  Not too bad, but thats about it.  Refreshing I guess.

12 oz. bottle.  Pours an orange color with pretty thick off white head that hangs around awhile and leaves some nice lacing around the glass.  Aroma is very nice.  Big piney, citrus hops along with some banana hit my nose.  Taste is hops and earthiness, maybe some leaves.  Finish is pretty dry and bitter.  Pretty good beer overall.

12 oz. bottle.   Pours dark brown with minimal tan head that doesnt last long.  Aroma is really good.  Toast, coffee, chocolate, raisins, some floral hops, and a small amount of alchohol can be recognized.  Taste is similar to aroma which is good.   Very creamy in the mouth and the hops finish it off with a nice bitter finish.  Ive had this beer before a long time ago and never rated it.   I forgot how good it was.  Im glad I gave it another try because this is a high quality brown ale.
